}}{{TIDTOC|adapter}} ==Overview== "UH-424 Rev:2.1" is silkscreened on the board used to populate this entry. Additionally, it is using '''ACON''' ([http://www.acon.com '''Advanced Connectek''']) USB connectors, a '''Wanjia''' WJ102-1C 5V relay, and multiple '''R.K.''' caps (5x 100 μF 16V, 1x 10 μF 16V, 1x 4.7 μF 50V ). :The device appears to be near identical to the [[D-Link DSB-H4 rev D2]] and clearly shares the same manufacturer.. which is currently presumed to be [http://web.archive.org/web/20030503002730/http://www.goodway.com.tw/en/product3.asp?listid=3&id=4&subid=7&pid=73&typeid=7 '''Good Way'''].
The '''Genesys Logic''' Hub IC package is marked with "GL650USB" and "0210E2AD1-35".
The power adapter included with the device appears to be a '''RadioShack''' branded EPA-101MU-05A (100-240VAC [50-60Hz] 0.3A -> 5V 2.5A).
